# .actrc — act local GitHub Actions runner configuration
#
# See: https://github.com/nektos/act
# Applied automatically when running `act` from this repository root.
#
# Use the ubuntu-latest image that mirrors the GitHub Actions hosted runner.
# The medium image (catthehacker/ubuntu:act-latest) is a good balance between
# image size and tool availability. Override with --platform if needed.
-P ubuntu-latest=catthehacker/ubuntu:act-latest

# Do not pull the container image automatically; test-local.sh controls refreshes.
--pull=false

# Reuse containers between runs to speed up repeated testing.
--reuse

# NOTE: --secret-file is NOT set here.
# scripts/test-local.sh adds --secret-file ${REPO_ROOT}/.secrets explicitly
# so the path resolves correctly regardless of the working directory.
# Running `act` directly (not via test-local.sh) requires --secret-file .secrets
# or creating the .secrets file and passing it on the command line.
